text: Amber Engels (born 28 December 1998) is a Belgian korfball player. She is a member of Putse KC and the Belgium national korfball team. Engels became a member of the national team in 2021. She won with the team the silver medal the 2021 European Korfball Championship and was during the tournament a topscorer for team. With the national team she won the silver medal at the 2022 World Games in Birmingham, Alabama. Engels graduated as a dietitian and continued another studies life sciences food industry. ==References== Category:1998 births Category:Living people Category:Belgian korfball players Category:sportswomen
